cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.COM, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of TV white space for backhaul in rural areas to provide broadband connectivity. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of TV white space for backhaul, which involves the transmission of information. This falls under the domain of information theory. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly discusses TV white space regulations, which may involve security and privacy concerns. This falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
4. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the challenge of providing broadband connectivity to a billion plus population in India, which has social and economic implications. This falls under the domain of computers and society. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the deployment of a testbed that provides broadband access to rural populations, which may involve multimedia applications. This falls under the domain of multimedia.
